/wiki/STAR_One: Star One was an Indian pay television network based in Mumbai. It was launched on 1 November 2004 and it was owned by Star TV and distributed worldwide by Fox International Channels. In November 2006, Star One was launched in the UK on Sky.
/wiki/C.I.D._(Indian_TV_series): CID is an Indian police procedural television series about Maharashtra and Mumbai's Crime Investigation Department, created by B. P. Singh for Sony Entertainment Television India. The series stars Shivaji Satam as ACP Pradyuman, Aditya Srivastava and Dayanand Shetty as Senior Inspectors Abhijeet and Daya, Dinesh Phadnis as Inspector Fredricks and Narendra Gupta as forensic expert Dr. Salunkhe.

/wiki/Raat_Hone_Ko_Hai: Raat Hone Ko Hai is an Indian television horror series that premiered on Sahara Manoranjan on May 10, 2004.
/wiki/Sahara_One: Sahara One was an Indian Hindi general entertainment channel based in New Delhi. It is operated by Sahara India Pariwar.
/wiki/Har_Ghar_Kuch_Kehta_Hai: Har Ghar Kuch Kehta Hai is a Hindi television serial that aired on Zee TV from 16 July 2007 – 18 April 2008. It was based on the story of 3 girls: Prarthna, Sidhhi, and Sanskriti. Even though they all have different lives and a different outlook of life, destiny is not always on their side, and when the unexpected happens their dreams, hopes and desires come crashing down.
/wiki/Zee_TV: Zee TV is an Indian pay television channel owned by Zee Entertainment Enterprises, a media and entertainment company based in Mumbai, Maharashtra. A part of the Essel Group, it started to broadcast on 2 October 1992 as the first Hindi-language subscription channel in India.
/wiki/Miley_Jab_Hum_Tum: Miley Jab Hum Tum (When We Met) is an Indian Teen drama television series that aired on STAR One from 22 September 2008 to 19 November 2010. The show is about falling in love during college and developing relations for a lifetime.
/wiki/Hitler_Didi: Hitler Didi (English: literally Hitler Sister but figuratively Auntie Hitler) is a daily Indian soap opera that aired on Zee TV. It premiered on 7 November 2011. The story is located in the backdrop of Delhi.  It airs in Pakistan on Express Entertainment. It also airs in Persian on Gem Bollywood as same name Hitler Didi.
/wiki/Begusarai_(TV_series): Begusarai is a daily soap opera that aired from Monday to Friday at 10:00 pm Indian standard time on &TV. The show premiered on 2 March 2015 and ended on 24 June 2016. It starred Shweta Tiwari, Shivangi Joshi, Satraj Gill and Vishal Aditya Singh in lead roles.The show is set in Begusarai, Bihar. The show was produced by Swastik Pictures (Swastik Productions Pvt. Ltd.).
/wiki/&TV: &TV (And TV) is a Hindi language entertainment channel owned by Zee Entertainment Enterprises. Launched as a General Entertainment Channel from ZEEL group, it started broadcasting on 2 March 2015.
/wiki/Porus_(TV_series): Porus is a historical drama television series based on the Battle of the Hydaspes, visualizing the lives of Indian warrior and ruler Porus, King of the Pauravas and Alexander The Great, King of the Macedonian Empire. It premiered on 27 November 2017 on Sony TV. It aired its last episode on 13 November 2018. Another historical drama Chandragupta Maurya replaced it with seamless continuity of story.
/wiki/Nazar_(TV_series): Nazar (Evil Eye) is an Indian supernatural television series which airs on Star Plus and streams on Hotstar. Produced by Gul Khan and Karishma Jain under 4 Lions Films, it is directed by Atif Khan and written by Mrinal Jha.
/wiki/Star_Plus: StarPlus is an Indian pay television channel owned by Star India. The network's programming consists of family dramas, comedies, youth-oriented reality shows, shows on crime and television films. It is also distributed internationally by The Walt Disney Company India, subsidiary of The Walt Disney Company.
/wiki/Divya_Drishti: Divya Drishti is an Indian supernatural drama television series which premiered on 23 February 2019 on Star Plus aired during weekends. Produced under Fireworks Productions, it stars Sana Sayyad, Nyra Banerjee, Sangita Ghosh, Adhvik Mahajan and Mishkat Varma.
/wiki/Tenali_Rama_(TV_series): Tenali Rama is an Indian historical comedy drama  based on the life of the legendary Telugu poet Tenali Ramakrishna, one of the Ashtadiggajas (or the eight honorable) poets at the court of Vijayanagara Emperor Krishnadevaraya (CE. 1509–1529), who is often cited as the greatest Vijayanagara emperor. The series premiered on SAB TV on 11 July 2017.
/wiki/Sony_Sab: Sony SAB (formerly SAB TV) stylised as SONY SAB is an Indian pay television channel owned by Sony Pictures Networks and specialising in comedy shows and soap operas.
/wiki/Dangal_TV: Dangal (Devanagari: दंगल) is a Hindi language general entertainment channel that broadcast the original programmes along with shows of some popular channels and off late shows.
/wiki/Rati_Pandey: Rati Pandey is an Indian actress known for her performances in Porus, Hitler Didi, Miley Jab Hum Tum, Begusarai, Har Ghar Kuch Kehta Hai and Shaadi Street.
